<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using elimination.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{9}{x}+{9}{y}=-{9}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle-{8}{x}-{6}{y}=-{10}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="8" /></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left({8},-{9}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to use the first equation to eliminate x from the second equation.</p>
<p>To eliminate we need the scaled version of equation one to have a coefficient of --8. So we scale by <m>\displaystyle--\frac{{8}}{{9}}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-\frac{{-{8}}}{{9}}{\left({9}{x}+{9}{y}\right)}=-\frac{{-{8}}}{{9}}{\left(-{9}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{\left(-{8}\right)}{x}+{8}{y}=-{8}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{8}{x}-{6}{y}=-{10}</m></p>
<p>Adding these two equations gives us</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{2}{y}=-{18}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-\frac{{18}}{{2}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-{9}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{9}{x}+{9}{\left(-{9}\right)}=-{9}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{9}{x}+{\left(-{81}\right)}=-{9}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{9}{x}=-{9}-{\left(-{81}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{9}{x}={72}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{72}}{{9}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}={8}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left({8},-{9}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

